paragraph.content:
in relation to an assessment agency, whether the agency is competent to
                        assess the skills, knowledge or experience acquired by individuals in
                        relation to an industry or a branch of an industry;

in relation to a learning programme, whether the programme meets a
                        standard to achieve the objectives of the programme as claimed by its
                        operator;

in relation to a qualification, whether the skills, knowledge or
                        experience recognized by the qualification meet a particular standard;
                        and

subsection.def:
member
                    (成員) means an appointed or ex officio member
                of the Council;

paragraph.content:
establish a committee to conduct the review and to make general
                    recommendations to the Council on any matter arising from the review;
                    and

may determine any matter of practice or procedure relating to the relevant
                    review where no provision governing such matter is made in this Ordinance or in
                    any rules made under section 22(2)(aa);

may receive and consider any material, whether by way of oral evidence,
                    written statements, documents or otherwise, and whether or not it would be
                    admissible in a court of law;

provide further information to the review committee and request the review
                    committee to answer any further question that the Council thinks fit;
                    and
